Active Directory and DNS

ADDS- Active Directory Domain Services - contains infomation such as user accounts and computers on the network

Common DNS record types
A - address record name to IPv4
CNAME - canonical name record, alias one name to another
AAAA - address record to resolve ipv6 to name
PTR- pointer record IPv4 to name (inverse query)
MX- mail exchange, email
SRV= service locator find conference servers and sip servers

Active Directory Domain Services can store DNS records so users can do things such as, accessing an IP address from a domain name, access a domain name from an IP address

DNS can use TCP or UDP depending on the size of the packet
Authoritative Name Servers store information about domai nnames and their IP addresses. 
